canonical:
  title: 甲子歲予謫眞安縣事將有不側者自分必死擬古人自挽而銘之
  author: 洪彦忠
  language: lzh
  text: 大明天下日先照國男子姓洪名忠字直半生迂拙文字之攻在世卅有二年而終命何云短意何其長卜于古縣茂林之鄕雲山在上灣碕在下千秋萬歲誰過斯野指點徘佪其必有悵然者矣
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 甲子歲予謫眞安縣事將有不側者自分必死擬古人自挽而銘之
  author: 洪彦忠
  language: lzh
  text: 大明天下。日先照國。男子姓洪。名忠字直。半生迂拙。文字之攻。在世卅有二年而終。命何云短。意何其長。卜于古縣。茂林之鄕。雲山在上。灣碕在下。千秋萬歲。誰過斯野。指點徘佪。其必有悵然者矣。
korean:
  title: 갑자년에 내가 진안현으로 귀양하게 되었는데, 일이 장차 불측의 화가 있어 반드시 죽을 것만 같기로, 옛사람이 스스로 만사하는 것에 비해서 명을 짓는다
  author: 홍언충
  language: kor
  text: 대명(大明) 천하로 해가 먼저 비치는 나라에 남자의 성은 홍(洪)이요, 이름은 충(忠)이요, 자는 직(直)이라, 반평생이 오활하고 졸해서 문자만을 배웠도다. 세상에서 32년을 살고 끝마치니, 명은 어찌 이다지도 짧은데 뜻은 어찌 이다지도 길단 말인가. 옛 무림현(茂林縣) 고을에 묻으니, 운산(雲山)은 위에 있고 강물은 아래 있다. 천추 만세에 누가 이 벌을 지내려나. 손가락질하고 서성대며 반드시 서글퍼하는 자가 있을 것이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1540_010_0160&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: 'An Epitaph for Myself: Written in the Year of Kapja, When Exiled to Jinan County, Facing Uncertain Calamity and Certain Death'
  author: Hong Eonchung
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Under the Great Ming's heaven and earth, where the sun first shines upon this land—there lived a man of the Hong clan, named Chung, courtesy name Jik. Half his life spent in awkward simplicity, devoted only to the written word. Thirty-two years he walked this world, then came to his end. Why was fate so brief? Yet why did longing stretch so long?

    In that ancient county of thick forests he was laid to rest, where clouds gather on the mountains above and waters bend below. Through ten thousand ages, who will pass through this wild place? Pointing fingers, lingering footsteps—surely there will be those who pause with sorrow.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: 'Jinan County (진안현): The author was exiled to this county, which inspired this self-written epitaph in anticipation of his death.'
  - key: ''
    value: 'Thirty-two years: The author''s stated age at the time of writing, presenting the brevity of his life as ironic against his enduring literary ambitions.'
  - key: ''
    value: 'The mountains above, waters below: A classical trope representing the eternal, unchanging natural world that will outlast human memory.'
